The paper proposes a novel approach for point cloud feature learning and understanding using convolutional neural networks. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), and the proposed approach involves interpolation and normalization techniques that are often used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on shape classification and segmentation, which are common topics in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper uses semantic parsing, which is a natural language processing technique (cs.CL), to analyze indoor scenes.
